ce:section.ce:para:
To measure the performance of the photoanodes of CQDs/TiO2 photosensitized solar cells were assembled in triplicate and by analyzing their I–V curve were obtained the average values of open circuit voltage (VOC), maximum power (Wmax), conversion efficiency (

                              η

                        ) and short-circuit current multiplied by the cell area to be presented as short-circuit current density (Jsc). These photoanodes were namely as follows in function to the CQDs concentrations: E−0 (Df 0), E−1 (Df 1), E−2 (Df 2).
